        "content": "<p>If I have a <code>f : U → V → W</code> in the parameter list. I know that the type of <code>f u</code> is <code>V → W</code>. How can I get <code>f v</code> whose type is <code>U → W</code>?</p>\n<p>Maybe it can be expressed as<code>fun u =&gt; op u v</code>? Is there existed syntactic sugar for it?</p>",
        "id": 462954404,
        "sender_full_name": "fra guu",
        "timestamp": 1723883701
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>(f · v)</code></p>",
        "id": 462954588,
        "sender_full_name": "Yaël Dillies",
        "timestamp": 1723883790
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks!</p>",
        "id": 462954973,
        "sender_full_name": "fra guu",
        "timestamp": 1723884203
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"725842\">fra guu</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
        "id": 462954977,
        "sender_full_name": "Notification Bot",
        "timestamp": 1723884207
